# Tickets CYX

A premium Discord ticket management bot built for fast support systems, organized moderation, and clean automation. Tickets CYX focuses on performance, clean UI responses, and a modern ticket workflow suitable for public communities and support servers.

Developed by CyeroX Development Team.

Discord Community
https://discord.gg/veEr2BK8NA

Overview

Tickets CYX provides a complete support ticket system for Discord servers. The bot creates private support channels, manages staff interactions, logs transcripts, and keeps ticket operations organized.

The system uses slash commands, buttons, and modals to deliver a smooth user experience. All responses appear in clean embeds with consistent design.

Key Features

• Full ticket management system
• Interactive setup command
• Multiple ticket button types
• Private support channels
• Ticket claim system for staff
• Add and remove users inside tickets
• Lock and unlock ticket channels
• HTML transcript generation
• Ticket statistics command
• Ticket logs system
• Premium styled embed responses
• Advanced help menu with buttons
• Modular bot structure using cogs and events
• JSON based local storage
• Clean and scalable code design

Ticket System

Tickets CYX creates private support channels when users press ticket buttons.

Ticket flow

• User presses ticket panel button
• Bot creates private support channel
• Staff role receives notification
• Support staff manage ticket with buttons
• Transcript generated before ticket deletion

Ticket Controls

• Create Ticket
• Close Ticket
• Delete Ticket
• Claim Ticket
• Add User
• Remove User
• Lock Ticket
• Unlock Ticket
• Generate Transcript

Commands

Ticket Commands

/ticket setup
Interactive setup command. Creates the ticket panel with custom embed and buttons.

/ticket panel
Send ticket panel again.

/ticket close
Close the current ticket.

/ticket delete
Delete the current ticket.

/ticket rename
Rename the ticket channel.

/ticket add
Add a member to the ticket.

/ticket remove
Remove a member from the ticket.

/ticket logs
Set the logs channel.

/ticket category
Set the ticket category.

/ticket role
Set the support role.

/ticket stats
Display ticket statistics.

Help Command

/help

Features

• Button based navigation
• Category based command view
• Clean embed interface
• Usage examples for commands

