Requirements

• Python 3.12 or newer
• Discord Bot Token
• Basic Discord developer setup

Python Libraries

discord.py
python-dotenv
aiofiles

requirements.txt example

```
discord.py
python-dotenv
aiofiles
```

Installation

Step 1

Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/tickets-cyx.git
cd tickets-cyx
```

Step 2

Install dependencies

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Step 3

Create the .env file

```
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
BOT_NAME=Tickets CYX
BOT_STATUS=Watching your support requests
OWNER_ID=your_discord_id
```

Step 4

Run the bot

```
python app.py
```

Configuration

Server administrators must run the setup command to configure the ticket system.

Run

/ticket setup

Setup wizard will ask for

• Ticket panel title
• Panel description
• Embed color
• Ticket category
• Support role
• Ticket buttons with emojis

After setup the bot sends a ticket panel where users create support tickets.

Permissions

Administrator permission required for setup and management commands.

Support staff role manages ticket channels.

Data Storage

Tickets CYX stores ticket information inside local JSON files.

Stored data includes

• Ticket owner
• Channel ID
• Ticket status
• Guild information

